Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.42,0:02:38.92,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,There are people inside of him...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.55,0:02:41.14,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,They want our help.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.14,0:02:43.43,Default,Lin,0000,0000,0000,,No! They're monsters!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.51,0:02:45.14,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.06,0:02:47.18,Default,Lin,0000,0000,0000,,Pull yourself together!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.18,0:02:48.68,Default,Lin,0000,0000,0000,,They're monsters!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.31,0:02:51.35,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Kill me!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.35,0:02:52.48,Default,Boy,0000,0000,0000,,Mommy!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.48,0:02:54.02,Default,Mom,0000,0000,0000,,Please! Give me back my child!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.94,0:02:56.65,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up! Stop it!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.65,0:02:57.73,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.73,0:02:58.78,Default,Guy2,0000,0000,0000,,It hurts...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.32,0:03:00.65,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Help me!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.65,0:03:01.82,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I said, "Stop it!"
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.49,0:03:02.66,Default-alt,Nina,0000,0000,0000,,Ed.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.24,0:03:05.33,Default,Nina,0000,0000,0000,,Let's play.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.08,0:03:09.12,Default,Nina,0000,0000,0000,,Let's play.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.25,0:03:14.79,Default,Envy,0000,0000,0000,,Playtime's over.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.43,0:03:28.64,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Damn...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.22,0:03:30.73,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,...it...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.07,0:03:38.94,Default,Woman,0000,0000,0000,,Help me...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.94,0:03:41.90,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,You don't understand the pain...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.90,0:03:43.41,Default,Lin,0000,0000,0000,,Ed! Wake up!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.03,0:03:45.41,Default,Lin,0000,0000,0000,,Come to your senses!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.41,0:03:46.95,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Join us!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.12,0:03:47.87,Default,Lin,0000,0000,0000,,Ed!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.25,0:03:54.12,Default,Lin,0000,0000,0000,,Ed!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.30,0:03:59.63,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Good! Good!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.17,0:04:01.22,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,All right, bring it over this way!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.47,0:04:02.97,Default,Guy2,0000,0000,0000,,Oh yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.55,0:04:06.68,Default,Guy2,0000,0000,0000,,I saw it over by the waste plant earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.10,0:04:10.22,Default,Guy2,0000,0000,0000,,If I recall, it was with some huge guy in an armor.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.47,0:04:11.56,Default,May,0000,0000,0000,,Armor?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.81,0:04:14.19,Default,May,0000,0000,0000,,Don't tell me it's the one from yesterday!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.44,0:04:21.74,Default,May,0000,0000,0000,,I'll never forgive him for kidnapping Shao May!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.74,0:04:23.90,Default,May,0000,0000,0000,,Demon! Devil! Loincloth!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.08,0:04:33.41,Default,May,0000,0000,0000,,There she is! Shao Ma-
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.41,0:04:34.29,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,Wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.58,0:04:39.17,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,That fat one...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.80,0:04:42.34,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,If I recall, they called him a Homunculus.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.34,0:04:43.76,Default,May,0000,0000,0000,,Homunculus?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.80,0:04:47.43,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,Their regeneration ability matches that of an immortal.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.43,0:04:49.30,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,We can't jump in carelessly.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.30,0:04:50.89,Default,May,0000,0000,0000,,Immortal?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.89,0:04:53.56,Default,May,0000,0000,0000,,This is my chance! Let's go after him!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.56,0:04:56.65,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,I told you. He's not an easy opponent.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.99,0:05:05.36,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,Why are those two together?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.74,0:05:13.54,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.04,0:05:16.33,Default,May,0000,0000,0000,,This place... is strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.33,0:05:19.63,Default,May,0000,0000,0000,,I've had a feeling that something was out of place, ever since I arrived in this country, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.92,0:05:21.21,Default,May,0000,0000,0000,,This is...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.92,0:05:28.09,Default,May,0000,0000,0000,,There are things crawling beneath my feet... and a lot of them...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.10,0:05:40.48,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong? Are you cold?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.57,0:05:42.61,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,You okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.61,0:05:46.99,Default,Glut,0000,0000,0000,,This way.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.58,0:06:02.50,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,I never would've thought something like this was under Central...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.14,0:06:13.26,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,W-What the heck is this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.27,0:06:17.73,Default,Glut,0000,0000,0000,,That was done by the gatekeepers.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.73,0:06:19.14,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Gatekeepers?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.14,0:06:21.98,Default,Glut,0000,0000,0000,,They won't attack you if you're with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.36,0:06:29.49,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,There's something up there.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.74,0:06:35.04,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Do we still have a long way to go?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.49,0:06:37.54,Default,Glut,0000,0000,0000,,A long way.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.79,0:06:39.71,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,We're meeting your father, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.71,0:06:42.29,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,He knows where people go after you swallow them, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.54,0:06:45.55,Default,Glut,0000,0000,0000,,Father knows everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.21,0:06:50.63,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Brother... You're alive, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.68,0:06:52.68,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Brother...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.03,0:07:13.12,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.78,0:07:17.66,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,A red... stone?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.00,0:07:22.25,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Right, Envy's core.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.96,0:07:24.25,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,A philosopher's stone.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.67,0:07:30.67,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,After all the time we spent looking for one,\Nthere's one right in front of me...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.69,0:07:45.19,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Let me out, Envy!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.19,0:07:46.61,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,It stinks in here!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.61,0:07:47.61,Default,Envy,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.94,0:07:50.11,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,We may be able to get out of here!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.57,0:07:53.57,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Let's work together, Envy!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.76,0:08:15.22,Default,May,0000,0000,0000,,What in the world are these?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.43,0:08:17.18,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,They are chimera.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.33,0:08:46.08,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,There's no end to them.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.79,0:08:48.00,Default,May,0000,0000,0000,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.09,0:08:53.17,Default,May,0000,0000,0000,,As I thought... there's something beneath us...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.63,0:08:54.59,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,Are they chimera?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.22,0:08:56.80,Default,May,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.80,0:09:00.76,Default,May,0000,0000,0000,,Is this... a person?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.47,0:09:04.85,Default,Glut,0000,0000,0000,,Father made us all!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.85,0:09:08.19,Default,Glut,0000,0000,0000,,Me, Lust, and Envy!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.91,0:09:23.04,Default,Father,0000,0000,0000,,It's loud up there.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.08,0:09:27.04,Default,Father,0000,0000,0000,,Someone's coming...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.71,0:09:39.80,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,I don't remember my parents' names, their faces, or even my own name.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.80,0:09:44.64,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,No... I don't remember if I was abandoned or sold before I had even been given a name.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.89,0:09:51.02,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Which one of you will lead this country?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.02,0:09:54.28,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Will it be you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.94,0:09:58.78,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,We were called the "Führer President Candidates".
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.45,0:10:03.79,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,And we were all gathered into one place and educated in many different fields.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.41,0:10:07.62,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,How to be a good emperor, anthropology...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.62,0:10:12.17,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,We were trained in military combat, marksmanship, and swordsmanship until we were highly capable.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.52,0:10:29.69,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Don't sweat it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.23,0:10:33.90,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,He was just a pawn for you to achieve your goal.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.07,0:10:38.15,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,"I will lead this country someday."
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.65,0:10:42.41,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,With that thought in mind,\NI endured the toughest of trainings.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.92,0:10:53.21,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,He was no good either.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.59,0:10:54.46,Default,Guy2,0000,0000,0000,,Next.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.97,0:11:00.59,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Lie down here.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.76,0:11:06.72,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,Umm... What is this about?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.22,0:11:08.93,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Relax.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.31,0:11:11.23,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,It'll be over soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.40,0:11:15.98,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,What are you planning to do?! Those bodies are...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.74,0:11:22.57,Default,Father,0000,0000,0000,,This is the twelfth one, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.66,0:11:27.70,Default,Father,0000,0000,0000,,Are you the one...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.95,0:11:29.37,Default,Father,0000,0000,0000,,...who will receive my wrath?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.17,0:11:39.34,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,A philosopher's stone is a high energy substance that includes the souls of many humans.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.34,0:11:45.18,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,As it enters a human's body, it goes on a rampage and tries to take over.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.93,0:11:56.98,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,The destruction and reconstruction by the stone is repeated until either the body dies or wins.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.82,0:12:00.07,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,Eventually...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.07,0:12:01.86,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.86,0:12:03.70,Default,Guy2,0000,0000,0000,,A new species of life!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.70,0:12:04.82,Default,Guy3,0000,0000,0000,,Congratulations.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.12,0:12:09.04,Default,Guy3,0000,0000,0000,,You've been selected to be the man who will lead this country.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.04,0:12:12.33,Default,Guy3,0000,0000,0000,,He will prepare everything you may need.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.91,0:12:14.71,Default,Guy3,0000,0000,0000,,From this day on, your name shall be...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.63,0:12:17.54,Default,Guy3,0000,0000,0000,,King Bradley!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.59,0:12:26.51,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,All that was left was a soul and the emotion of wrath.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.51,0:12:35.69,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,I don't even know if this soul belongs to someone who was turned into the stone, or if it was mine to begin with.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.73,0:12:49.16,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,If you were human, couldn't you live as a human instead of a Homunculus, sir?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.41,0:12:52.41,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,You're telling me to go back to being a human?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.12,0:12:54.66,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,That's impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.66,0:12:58.17,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,This body has far surpassed human capabilities.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.42,0:13:00.88,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,It's far superior.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.67,0:13:10.18,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,Just as how you humans are proud to be human,\Nwe are proud to be Homunculi.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.01,0:13:15.39,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure that woman took that pride to her death, as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.77,0:13:18.44,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Ow.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.69,0:13:20.27,Default,Lin,0000,0000,0000,,Just something temporary.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.27,0:13:21.61,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.69,0:13:26.70,Default,Envy,0000,0000,0000,,I've collected all the ones around here.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.99,0:13:30.70,Default,Lin,0000,0000,0000,,Are these all from Xerxes?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.70,0:13:32.08,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.08,0:13:35.25,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,It's a portion of the mural that was in a temple in the ruins.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.58,0:13:40.13,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,When I first saw it,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.13,0:13:45.72,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I thought it was a transmutation circle for a philosopher's stone, like the one beneath Research Laboratory 5.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.26,0:13:48.05,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,But I was wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.05,0:13:49.72,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,The sun represents the soul.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.14,0:13:51.97,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,The moon represents the mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.68,0:13:56.98,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,And this stone which has the mural on it. This represents the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.98,0:14:01.02,Default,Lin,0000,0000,0000,,Come on... explain it so I can understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.02,0:14:03.98,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Basically, what was drawn there...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.44,0:14:06.24,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,...is a circle for human transmutation.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.44,0:14:07.82,Default,Lin,0000,0000,0000,,Human transmutation?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.49,0:14:10.99,Default,Lin,0000,0000,0000,,So that means, to raise the dead...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.16,0:14:11.99,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.74,0:14:15.70,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,The principle of alchemy is equivalent exchange.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.70,0:14:20.17,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,One cannot create a soul that doesn't exist in this world, at least through alchemy.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.17,0:14:22.00,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I've confirmed that.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.55,0:14:27.26,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,So, I've thought of a way to get out of here.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.51,0:14:29.43,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,What if I transmute myself from scratch...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.01,0:14:32.64,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,A human that's alive?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.97,0:14:34.89,Default,Lin,0000,0000,0000,,Transmute from scratch?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.89,0:14:35.89,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.89,0:14:41.86,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I use this transmutation circle to decompose myself, then put myself back together.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.86,0:14:43.65,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,That's also human transmutation.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.65,0:14:45.15,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,The gate should open.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.11,0:14:49.15,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,If Gluttony is a fake Gate of Truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.15,0:14:53.91,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,shouldn't we be able to get to\Nthe real world by going through the real gate?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.29,0:14:59.41,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I'll open the gate; you guys leap in.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.62,0:15:01.42,Default,Envy,0000,0000,0000,,What if this doesn't work?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.92,0:15:03.46,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Then we suffer from rebound.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.46,0:15:07.05,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,All of the effects of the rebound go to the one who attempted it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.05,0:15:09.05,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,In this case, me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.97,0:15:12.59,Default,Lin,0000,0000,0000,,I know nothing about alchemy.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.22,0:15:14.18,Default,Lin,0000,0000,0000,,I'll leave it to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.18,0:15:15.18,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.22,0:15:19.81,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,So, Envy, there's something I need to ask you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.73,0:15:28.36,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,The mural I saw at Xerxes looked like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.40,0:15:31.86,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I'm curious about this symbol.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.86,0:15:35.03,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,It's the word representing God, but flipped over.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.03,0:15:37.41,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,And the dragon with two heads.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.87,0:15:40.75,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,This represents the perfect being.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.33,0:15:47.38,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,This means "I will cast God from the Heavens to the Earth, and become the perfect being."
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.38,0:15:50.17,Default,Lin,0000,0000,0000,,People think of outrageous things.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.17,0:15:52.09,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,It would be wonderful if they had only thought about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.63,0:15:53.76,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,The problem here is...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.59,0:15:56.76,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,...this part, which is broken off.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.14,0:16:00.64,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,A lion that swallows the sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.64,0:16:02.89,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,This represents the philosopher's stone.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.02,0:16:06.73,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,And the ingredients of philosopher's stones are live humans.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.44,0:16:08.73,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Right, Envy?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.11,0:16:10.69,Default,Envy,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, you're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.74,0:16:16.32,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Why did the nation of Xerxes,\Na nation so prosperous, perish overnight?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.08,0:16:18.87,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Where did its citizens go?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.87,0:16:23.00,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't a portion of the ruins in here to cover up the evidence?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.21,0:16:31.09,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,You guys turned all of Xerxes' citizens into a philosopher's stone, didn't you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.31,0:16:45.65,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Who did it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.48,0:16:48.73,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Who transmuted themselves?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.73,0:16:53.36,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Who's the one who turned all of the country's people into a philosopher's stone for tremendous power...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.36,0:16:56.66,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,...for the sole purpose of becoming a being that would surpass God?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.82,0:16:58.91,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Is it the "Father" that you talked about?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.12,0:17:07.42,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that guy trying to recreate that event in this country by using you guys, the Homunculi?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.71,0:17:10.67,Default,Envy,0000,0000,0000,,I'll tell you if you get us out of here.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.96,0:17:17.59,Default,Envy,0000,0000,0000,,Let's stop beating around the bush, Fullmetal Alchemist.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.59,0:17:22.31,Default,Envy,0000,0000,0000,,You need a toll if you're going to open the gate, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.68,0:17:25.94,Default,Envy,0000,0000,0000,,Use it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.44,0:17:30.90,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Help me!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.86,0:17:31.98,Default-alt,Guy2,0000,0000,0000,,Please, just kill me!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.69,0:17:36.45,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,These are all people from Xerxes, aren't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.70,0:17:43.45,Default,Envy,0000,0000,0000,,{\fscx97}Their bodies and minds have rotted away in the ancient past, and they are beings who are solely used as an energy source.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.75,0:17:47.12,Default,Envy,0000,0000,0000,,They don't even remember what they used to look like.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.79,0:17:49.25,Default,Envy,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sympathizing with them?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.25,0:17:50.96,Default,Envy,0000,0000,0000,,What a stupid emotion.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.50,0:17:57.59,Default,Envy,0000,0000,0000,,{\fscx88}The sole reason you want to think of them as humans is that you want to believe that your brother, who's only a soul, is human, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.68,0:18:04.77,Default,Envy,0000,0000,0000,,You hesitate to set fire to coal because you feel sorry for a tree that died ages ago?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.27,0:18:08.35,Default,Envy,0000,0000,0000,,They can't return to being human anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.52,0:18:13.69,Default,Envy,0000,0000,0000,,Lay down a definition for a human with logic and not emotion, alchemist.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.62,0:18:21.62,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.58,0:18:28.87,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Lin, if something happens to me,\Ntell everyone about what these guys are up to.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.17,0:18:33.92,Default,Lin,0000,0000,0000,,Whatever happens to Amestris isn't my problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.92,0:18:35.51,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.22,0:18:40.01,Default,Lin,0000,0000,0000,,There are people precious to you waiting for you in that country, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.01,0:18:43.22,Default,Lin,0000,0000,0000,,Get out of here alive and tell them yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.64,0:18:52.90,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry. Please let me use your souls.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.40,0:18:58.03,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Let's do this!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.49,0:19:06.12,Default,Lin,0000,0000,0000,,I thought that pose of putting their hands together looked similar to something...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.20,0:19:09.62,Default,Lin,0000,0000,0000,,It's almost like a prayer to God.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.38,0:19:22.64,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,It's been a while since I've done this.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.30,0:19:26.06,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I never thought I'd open it again... under this situation.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.64,0:19:28.64,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Lin! Jump in!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.06,0:19:33.65,Default,Lin,0000,0000,0000,,I'm counting on you, alchemist!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.82,0:19:39.53,Default,Lin,0000,0000,0000,,This is the same sensation I felt while being swallowed by Gluttony...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.20,0:19:49.58,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.46,0:19:52.96,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.09,0:20:08.72,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,The body and the soul are connected by the mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.72,0:20:13.85,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,A part of my body is before the Gate of Truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.15,0:20:19.11,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,If I just let my mind guide me,\NI should be able to get to the gate...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.24,0:20:25.24,Default,Truth,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, so you didn't come here to get your body back?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.20,0:20:30.08,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Your father is through here, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.08,0:20:31.29,Default,Glut,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.91,0:20:34.71,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,I can find clues on how to find my brother...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.89,0:20:51.93,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,All right, I'm here.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.15,0:20:59.36,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Why are there two gates?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.01,0:21:26.72,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Al!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.76,0:21:29.93,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Al! Come here!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.60,0:21:32.97,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry up! Al!!!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.77,0:21:35.35,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Al!!!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.85,0:21:36.73,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,I can't.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.15,0:21:40.48,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,You're not my soul.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.23,0:21:42.73,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,I can't go with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.05,0:22:09.09,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Alphonse!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.10,0:22:12.93,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Alphonse!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.93,0:22:14.39,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Alphonse!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.06,0:22:17.77,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Someday, I'll come and bring you back.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.56,0:22:19.77,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Wait for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.56,0:22:23.57,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Wait for me!!!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.74,0:24:05.13,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,{\fscx94}It is hard to find the shape of an illusion, like a wavering flame.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.67,0:24:10.97,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,{\fscx90}And a flame can be cruel at times, but can also be a flame of hope.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.59,0:24:17.01,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Next time, Fullmetal Alchemist:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.01,0:24:20.77,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Episode 27, Interlude Party.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.56,0:24:25.44,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,You mustn't be afraid of the darkness inside of you.
